article.headline: Oakland, Mich. 67, Duquesne 53
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Vova Severovas scored 22 points and Shawn Hopes had 20 to lead Oakland (Mich.) to a 67-53 victory over Duquesne on Wednesday. Hopes, a 6-foot-7-inch, 275-pound center, converted his first nine shots and finished 9 for 10 for Oakland (4-2), which out rebounded Duquesne (2-2) by 36-19 and shot 61.4 percent to the Dukes' 33.9. Severovas, a 6-foot-6-inch forward from Vilnius, Lithuania, shot 8 for 11 and scored 12 second-half points, when Oakland built a 49-29 lead. Duquesne got no closer than 12 points the rest of the way. Scott Grote led the Dukes with 13 points and Robert Mitchell added 10. Oakland led, 30-16, at halftime, holding Duquesne scoreless for a span of 8:18. Duquesne, playing through a season in which five of its players were injured in a Sept. 17 shooting incident on campus, had only one healthy player taller than 6 foot 6 inches. Hopes' performance against Duquesne followed that of 6-foot-11-inch James Hughes of Northern Illinois, who exploited the undersized Dukes on Monday in an 87-82 overtime victory by notching 25 points, eight rebounds and six blocked shots.
